This dish is perfect for potlucks. I don't serve it on greens, and reduce the cayenne to 1/4 tsp. Its hearty grain and delicate flavors comprise a dish that's a family favorite.

Rating: 4
This made me want to sing, it was so good. I did not use tomato or cucumber, but served on a small bed of baby greens with blanched broccoli. Guests described it as "light but hardy" and delicious, of course. Unless you like things really tart, I would cut back the lemon juice to between 1 T and 2.

